    BinaryPredicateImpl

    public class KbPredicateImpl
extends RelationImpl
implements com.cyc.kb.KbPredicate
    A KBPredicate object is a facade for a #$Predicate in Cyc KB. A predicate represents the property of a thing or the relationship between two or more things. Predicates are used to form #$CycLAtomicSentence and are in the 0th argument position. Well-formed (based on predicate arguments) and closed sentences can either be true or false.

      • findOrCreate

        public static KbPredicateImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId)
                                    throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                           com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a KBPredicate object named nameOrId. If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of #$Predicate. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already a #$Predicate, it will be returned. If it is not already a #$Predicate, but can be made into one by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into a #$Predicate by adding assertions (i.e. some existing assertion prevents it from being a #$Predicate), a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nameOrId - the string representation or the HLID of the #$Predicate
        Returns:
        a new KBPredicate
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException

      • findOrCreate

        public static KbPredicateImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId,
                           com.cyc.kb.KbCollection constraintCol)
                                    throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                           com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a KBPredicate object named nameOrId, and also make it an instance of constraintCol in the default context specified by KBAPIDefaultContext#forAssertion(). If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of both #$Predicate and constraintCol. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already both a #$Predicate and a constraintCol, it will be returned. If it is not already both a #$Predicate and a constraintCol, but can be made so by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into both a #$Predicate and a constraintCol by adding assertions, a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nameOrId - the string representation or the HLID of the #$Predicate
        constraintCol - the collection that this #$Predicate will instantiate
        Returns:
        a new KBPredicate
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
